<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-19T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-19T17:00:00-05:00" n="162" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1457</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-19T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 19,
                                            1918, 6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>75. Your 74, April 5, 6 p.m. Department approves Consul’s
                                facilitating and Embassy’s encouraging export of commodities from
                                Russia to America. Delivery of American commodities in exchange will
                                depend on reports requested from you and Consul General as to how
                                such American goods can be safeguarded from serving enemy purposes
                                or falling into enemy hands.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>